\left\{ \begin{array}{l}  xy - x - y = 1\\  4{x^3} - 12{x^2} + 9x =  - {y^3} + 6y + 7  \end{array} \right. ,\quad (x,y\in\mathbb{R}).
\left\{ \begin{array}{l}  yz=z+2\\  4z^3-3z+y^3-6y-6=0  \end{array} \right.\Leftrightarrow \left\{ \begin{array}{l}  yz=z+2\\  4z^3-3y^2z+y^3=0  \end{array} \right.
x=\frac {y+1}{y-1} 
